# Purpose: chronyd daemon command-line flags.
# Scope: chronyd.service startup environment (/etc/sysconfig/chronyd).
# Dependencies: /var/lib/chrony/drift (for the -s flag).
# Standard: chronyd(8).
#
# -s   Primary defense against the DNS-time deadlock. Floors the system clock
#      at startup to the driftfile mtime ("last time chronyd ran") — before
#      any hostname is resolved — so that TLS certificate validity checks
#      (chronyd's own NTS-KE, and any TLS-based DNS transport the local
#      resolver performs) can succeed even after a dead/reset RTC.
#
# -F 2 Seccomp system-call filter, level 2 (blocklist mode): blocks a small
#      set of high-risk syscalls such as fork/exec. Unlike the level-1
#      allowlist, it cannot kill chronyd on unexpected-but-benign libc/NSS
#      syscalls, at the cost of a weaker sandbox.

OPTIONS="-s -F 2"
